{
  "info": {
    "name": "EGYAKIN DirectChat — WebSocket Tests",
    "_postman_id": "dc-ws-001",
    "description": "Complete WebSocket test suite for the DirectChat Reverb/Pusher presence channels.\n\n## How to use\n1. Set collection variable `base_url` to your server (e.g. http://localhost:8000)\n2. Set `reverb_host` and `reverb_port` (default: localhost:8080)\n3. Run folder **0 – Auth** first to populate `token`, `token_b`, `socket_id_a`, `socket_id_b`\n4. Run folder **1 – Channel Auth** to get channel auth signatures\n5. Open two WebSocket tabs side-by-side (User A + User B) and run through folders 2–7\n\n## Architecture\n- Server: Laravel Reverb (Pusher-protocol compatible)\n- Channels: `presence-conversation.{id}` (requires auth)\n- All server-side events are triggered by REST calls in the companion REST collection\n- Typing is a server-sent event via POST /chat/conversations/{id}/typing",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",      "value": "http://localhost:8000/api/v3", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reverb_host",   "value": "localhost",                    "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reverb_port",   "value": "8080",                        "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reverb_app_key","value": "054d5cd586f42bbc529e880a574651d3", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token",         "value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "Bearer token for User A — set by folder 0" },
    { "key": "token_b",       "value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "Bearer token for User B — set by folder 0" },
    { "key": "socket_id_a",   "value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "WebSocket socket_id for User A — copy from WS connection_established event" },
    { "key": "socket_id_b",   "value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "WebSocket socket_id for User B — copy from WS connection_established event" },
    { "key": "channel_auth_a","value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "Channel auth string for User A — set by folder 1" },
    { "key": "channel_auth_b","value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "Channel auth string for User B — set by folder 1" },
    { "key": "channel_data_a","value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "Channel data JSON string for User A — set by folder 1" },
    { "key": "channel_data_b","value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "Channel data JSON string for User B — set by folder 1" },
    { "key": "conversation_id","value": "1","type": "string", "description": "Conversation ID to test — update after creating a conversation" },
    { "key": "message_id",    "value": "",  "type": "string", "description": "Message ID — set after sending a message" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0 – Auth (get tokens)",
      "description": "Login as two users to get Bearer tokens. Tokens are saved to collection variables `token` and `token_b`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login as User A",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.authorisation && res.authorisation.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.authorisation.token);",
                  "    console.log('User A token saved:', res.authorisation.token.substring(0,20) + '...');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Login successful', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Token present', () => pm.expect(res.authorisation).to.have.property('token'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user_a@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["login"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login as User B",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.authorisation && res.authorisation.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token_b', res.authorisation.token);",
                  "    console.log('User B token saved:', res.authorisation.token.substring(0,20) + '...');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Login successful', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Token present', () => pm.expect(res.authorisation).to.have.property('token'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user_b@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["login"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1 – Channel Auth (get signatures)",
      "description": "Authenticates both users for the presence channel. You must have `socket_id_a` and `socket_id_b` set from the WebSocket connection_established events before running these.\n\nThe `auth` and `channel_data` values returned here are what you paste into the pusher:subscribe message in the WebSocket tab.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Authenticate Channel — User A",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Auth returned', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Has auth field', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('auth'));",
                  "pm.test('Has channel_data field', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('channel_data'));",
                  "if (res.auth) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('channel_auth_a', res.auth);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('channel_data_a', res.channel_data);",
                  "    console.log('User A channel auth saved.');",
                  "    console.log('Use this in pusher:subscribe message:');",
                  "    console.log(JSON.stringify({ event: 'pusher:subscribe', data: { channel: 'presence-conversation.' + pm.collectionVariables.get('conversation_id'), auth: res.auth, channel_data: res.channel_data } }, null, 2));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"socket_id\": \"{{socket_id_a}}\",\n  \"channel_name\": \"presence-conversation.{{conversation_id}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/../broadcasting/auth",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["..", "broadcasting", "auth"]
            },
            "description": "IMPORTANT: Set `socket_id_a` collection variable first.\n\nGet your socket_id by connecting to ws://{{reverb_host}}:{{reverb_port}}/app/{{reverb_app_key}} in a Postman WebSocket tab. The server immediately sends a `pusher:connection_established` event containing the socket_id."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Authenticate Channel — User B",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Auth returned', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Has auth field', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('auth'));",
                  "if (res.auth) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('channel_auth_b', res.auth);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('channel_data_b', res.channel_data);",
                  "    console.log('User B channel auth saved.');",
                  "    console.log('Use this in pusher:subscribe message:');",
                  "    console.log(JSON.stringify({ event: 'pusher:subscribe', data: { channel: 'presence-conversation.' + pm.collectionVariables.get('conversation_id'), auth: res.auth, channel_data: res.channel_data } }, null, 2));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_b}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"socket_id\": \"{{socket_id_b}}\",\n  \"channel_name\": \"presence-conversation.{{conversation_id}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/../broadcasting/auth",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["..", "broadcasting", "auth"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Authenticate Channel — Non-member (expect 403)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Non-member is rejected (403)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer INVALID_OR_NON_MEMBER_TOKEN" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"socket_id\": \"000000.000\",\n  \"channel_name\": \"presence-conversation.{{conversation_id}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/../broadcasting/auth",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["..", "broadcasting", "auth"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2 – WebSocket Connection & Subscribe",
      "description": "These are INSTRUCTIONS for your WebSocket tabs — not REST requests.\n\nPostman WebSocket requests are created manually (New → WebSocket). The requests in this folder document the exact messages to send in each WebSocket tab.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "INSTRUCTION: Connect User A WebSocket",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "ws://{{reverb_host}}:{{reverb_port}}/app/{{reverb_app_key}}",
              "protocol": "ws",
              "host": ["{{reverb_host}}"],
              "port": "{{reverb_port}}",
              "path": ["app", "{{reverb_app_key}}"]
            },
            "description": "## How to create a WebSocket connection in Postman\n\n1. Click **New** (top left) → select **WebSocket**\n2. Enter URL: `ws://localhost:8080/app/054d5cd586f42bbc529e880a574651d3`\n3. Click **Connect**\n\n## Expected response immediately after connecting:\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"pusher:connection_established\",\n  \"data\": \"{\\\"socket_id\\\":\\\"123456.789\\\",\\\"activity_timeout\\\":120}\"\n}\n```\n\n**Copy the `socket_id` value** and save it as collection variable `socket_id_a`.\n\nThen run the **Channel Auth — User A** REST request in folder 1."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "INSTRUCTION: Subscribe User A to Channel",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event\": \"pusher:subscribe\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.{{conversation_id}}\",\n    \"auth\": \"{{channel_auth_a}}\",\n    \"channel_data\": \"{{channel_data_a}}\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "ws://{{reverb_host}}:{{reverb_port}}/app/{{reverb_app_key}}",
              "protocol": "ws",
              "host": ["{{reverb_host}}"],
              "port": "{{reverb_port}}",
              "path": ["app", "{{reverb_app_key}}"]
            },
            "description": "## Send this message in the User A WebSocket tab\n\nAfter getting channel auth from folder 1, paste this JSON into the **Message** field of your WebSocket tab and click **Send**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"pusher:subscribe\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.1\",\n    \"auth\": \"<value from channel_auth_a variable>\",\n    \"channel_data\": \"<value from channel_data_a variable>\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Expected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"pusher_internal:subscription_succeeded\",\n  \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.1\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"presence\": {\n      \"count\": 1,\n      \"ids\": [1],\n      \"hash\": { \"1\": { \"id\": 1, \"name\": \"Mohamed Ibrahim\", \"image\": \"...\" } }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "INSTRUCTION: Connect & Subscribe User B",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event\": \"pusher:subscribe\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.{{conversation_id}}\",\n    \"auth\": \"{{channel_auth_b}}\",\n    \"channel_data\": \"{{channel_data_b}}\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "ws://{{reverb_host}}:{{reverb_port}}/app/{{reverb_app_key}}",
              "protocol": "ws",
              "host": ["{{reverb_host}}"],
              "port": "{{reverb_port}}",
              "path": ["app", "{{reverb_app_key}}"]
            },
            "description": "## Open a SECOND Postman WebSocket tab for User B\n\n1. Click **New** → **WebSocket**\n2. URL: `ws://localhost:8080/app/054d5cd586f42bbc529e880a574651d3`\n3. Connect → copy socket_id → save as `socket_id_b`\n4. Run **Channel Auth — User B** in folder 1\n5. Send the subscribe message:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"pusher:subscribe\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.1\",\n    \"auth\": \"<value from channel_auth_b variable>\",\n    \"channel_data\": \"<value from channel_data_b variable>\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## When User B joins, User A's tab receives:\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"pusher_internal:member_added\",\n  \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.1\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"user_id\": 2,\n    \"user_info\": { \"id\": 2, \"name\": \"User B\", \"image\": \"...\" }\n  }\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Ping — Keep Connection Alive",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event\": \"pusher:ping\",\n  \"data\": {}\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "ws://{{reverb_host}}:{{reverb_port}}/app/{{reverb_app_key}}",
              "protocol": "ws",
              "host": ["{{reverb_host}}"],
              "port": "{{reverb_port}}",
              "path": ["app", "{{reverb_app_key}}"]
            },
            "description": "Send this in the WebSocket tab to keep the connection alive (Reverb/Pusher uses 120s activity timeout).\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{ \"event\": \"pusher:pong\", \"data\": {} }\n```"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3 – Test: message.sent event",
      "description": "Trigger message.sent by sending a message via REST. Both User A and User B WebSocket tabs should receive the event.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Send Text Message (triggers message.sent)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Message sent (201)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Has message id', () => pm.expect(res.data).to.have.property('id'));",
                  "if (res.data && res.data.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('message_id', res.data.id);",
                  "    console.log('message_id saved:', res.data.id);",
                  "}",
                  "console.log('');",
                  "console.log('✅ CHECK WebSocket tabs now!');",
                  "console.log('Both User A and User B tabs should receive:');",
                  "console.log(JSON.stringify({",
                  "    event: 'message.sent',",
                  "    channel: 'presence-conversation.' + pm.collectionVariables.get('conversation_id'),",
                  "    data: { message: { id: res.data && res.data.id, type: 'text', content: 'Hello from WebSocket test!', '...': '...' } }",
                  "}, null, 2));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"text\",\n  \"content\": \"Hello from WebSocket test!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/conversations/{{conversation_id}}/messages",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "conversations", "{{conversation_id}}", "messages"]
            },
            "description": "## Expected WebSocket event on BOTH tabs:\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"message.sent\",\n  \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.1\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"message\": {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"conversation_id\": 1,\n      \"sender\": { \"id\": 1, \"name\": \"Mohamed\", \"lname\": \"Ibrahim\", \"image\": \"...\", \"specialty\": \"...\" },\n      \"type\": \"text\",\n      \"content\": \"Hello from WebSocket test!\",\n      \"file_metadata\": null,\n      \"file_url\": null,\n      \"reply_to\": null,\n      \"reads\": [],\n      \"reads_count\": 0,\n      \"reactions\": [],\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-04-19T...\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-19T...\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Send Reply Message (triggers message.sent with reply_to)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Reply sent (201)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Has reply_to in response', () => pm.expect(res.data).to.have.property('reply_to'));",
                  "console.log('CHECK WebSocket: message.sent should include reply_to object');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_b}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"text\",\n  \"content\": \"This is a reply!\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": {{message_id}}\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/conversations/{{conversation_id}}/messages",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "conversations", "{{conversation_id}}", "messages"]
            },
            "description": "## Expected WebSocket event:\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"message.sent\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"message\": {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"type\": \"text\",\n      \"content\": \"This is a reply!\",\n      \"reply_to\": {\n        \"id\": 42,\n        \"type\": \"text\",\n        \"content\": \"Hello from WebSocket test!\",\n        \"sender_id\": 1,\n        \"sender\": { \"id\": 1, \"name\": \"Mohamed\", \"lname\": \"Ibrahim\" }\n      },\n      \"...\": \"...\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Send Image Message (triggers message.sent with file_url)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Image message sent (201)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Type is image', () => pm.expect(res.data.type).to.equal('image'));",
                  "pm.test('Has file_url', () => pm.expect(res.data.file_url).to.not.be.null);",
                  "console.log('CHECK WebSocket: message.sent should have file_url (signed URL, 30min expiry)');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                { "key": "type",  "value": "image", "type": "text" },
                { "key": "file",  "type": "file",   "description": "Select any image file (jpg/png/webp, max 10MB)" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/conversations/{{conversation_id}}/messages",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "conversations", "{{conversation_id}}", "messages"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4 – Test: user.typing event",
      "description": "Trigger user.typing via REST. The OTHER user's WebSocket tab should receive it (toOthers() excludes the sender).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "User A is Typing (User B tab should receive event)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Typing broadcast sent (200)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "console.log('');",
                  "console.log('✅ CHECK User B WebSocket tab!');",
                  "console.log('User B should receive:');",
                  "console.log(JSON.stringify({",
                  "    event: 'user.typing',",
                  "    channel: 'presence-conversation.' + pm.collectionVariables.get('conversation_id'),",
                  "    data: { conversation_id: +pm.collectionVariables.get('conversation_id'), user_id: 'User A id', user_name: 'User A name', is_typing: true }",
                  "}, null, 2));",
                  "console.log('User A tab should NOT receive it (toOthers()).');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"is_typing\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/conversations/{{conversation_id}}/typing",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "conversations", "{{conversation_id}}", "typing"]
            },
            "description": "## Expected event on User B tab only:\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"user.typing\",\n  \"channel\": \"presence-conversation.1\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"conversation_id\": 1,\n    \"user_id\": 1,\n    \"user_name\": \"Mohamed Ibrahim\",\n    \"is_typing\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**User A tab should NOT receive this** — the service uses `broadcast(...)->toOthers()`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "User A Stopped Typing (is_typing: false)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Typing stopped broadcast sent (200)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "console.log('CHECK User B tab: is_typing should be false');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept",        "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"is_typing\": false\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/conversations/{{conversation_id}}/typing",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
